The paper deals with the problem of online influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields such as social networks, machine learning, and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
